11/06/2003
MOSTAR, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Croatian Democratic Union (HDZ) in BiH and the Party of Democratic Action agreed to form a local government in Hercegovina-Neretva County, according to an HDZ statement issued Tuesday (10 June). Senior party officials discussed the government and ministerial candidates at a meeting late Monday. The parties, which represent Croat and Muslim constituencies, agreed to call a session of the county assembly as soon as possible to elect members of the local government. The parties will propose candidates in accordance with the number of seats held by minority parties in the local parliament. (FENA, BBC - 10/06/03)
